Q6. JavaScript as a Backend Language

JavaScript is not only used on the frontend; it is widely used on the backend using environments like Node.js.

Performance

Node.js uses event-driven, non-blocking architecture

Handles many requests at the same time efficiently

Suitable for real-time apps like chat, gaming, streaming

Ecosystem

Huge package library (npm) with thousands of ready-to-use modules

Same language for frontend and backend reduces learning curve

Strong community support and documentation

Popular backend frameworks

Node.js

Express.js

Nest.js

Next.js (full-stack framework)

AdonisJS

These frameworks help build REST APIs, authentication systems, real-time chat servers, dashboards, etc.
